snippet.textDisplay: You know that the studios don't get the full amount of the box office, right? The rough calculation is 60% of the domestic gross, and 40% overseas, give or take. And then you have to add the marketing costs (with a movie like this, easily we can say around $100 and $150 million), and then some bonuses that are not contemplated in the official budget (and could be between $10 and $50 million more). That's why a movie like Superman Returns didn't make any profit even when it got almost $400 million at the worldwide box office, with a budget of around $270 million. That's because it made almost $120 million in North America and $76 million in the rest of the world. That adds up as $240 million, and we are not even counting marketing and etc. So, yeah, surprise surprise, Disney didn't gross the $2.8 billion of Endgame, for example.

Either way Disney should take the deal. I love Spider-Man in the MCU, was so exited to see him in civil war and have been hooked ever since.
I just wonder if Disney can make up that 5 billion.

Then again, if Disney can get it for free they should go for it... and poor Sony.
